    "text": "Hip-hop music, characterized by rhythmic complexity and moderate tempo, may modulate prefrontal beta and gamma oscillations during Sudoku solving in adolescents.",
    "topic": "Neural oscillations"
  },
  {
    "text": "The prefrontal cortex generates beta and gamma oscillations that are measurable via electroencephalography (EEG) during tasks such as Sudoku, which require attention, working memory, and executive function.",
    "topic": "Prefrontal cortex activity"
  },
  {
    "text": "Background music is widely used during cognitive tasks, yet its effects on neural oscillatory activity during complex problem-solving in adolescent populations remain poorly characterized.",
    "topic": "Effects of background music"
  },
  {
    "text": "Sudoku solving involves attention, working memory, and executive function, all of which are orchestrated by the prefrontal cortex.",
    "topic": "Sudoku cognitive demands"
  },
  {
    "text": "Electroencephalography (EEG) is a method used to measure prefrontal beta and gamma oscillations during cognitive tasks such as Sudoku solving.",
